(A Charitable Remainder Annuity Trust \(CRAT\) is a trust structure that provides a fixed annuity to) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 10.50 Tf
0.145 0.169 0.204 rg
1 0 0 1 52.00 703.00 Tm
(one or more noncharitable beneficiaries, with the remainder interest passing to a designated charity.) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 10.50 Tf
0.145 0.169 0.204 rg
1 0 0 1 52.00 689.00 Tm
(The annuity is determined at the trust's inception based on the initial fair market value of the) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 10.50 Tf
0.145 0.169 0.204 rg
1 0 0 1 52.00 675.00 Tm
(trust assets and remains constant regardless of the trust's investment performance [1].) Tj
ET
BT
/F2 11.50 Tf
0.169 0.349 0.639 rg
1 0 0 1 52.00 653.00 Tm
(Structure and Funding) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 10.50 Tf
0.145 0.169 0.204 rg
1 0 0 1 52.00 630.00 Tm
(CRATs can be structured for the lifetime of the beneficiaries or for a term of years, with a maximum) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 10.50 Tf
0.145 0.169 0.204 rg
1 0 0 1 52.00 616.00 Tm
(term of 20 years as specified under 26 CFR §1.664-2 [1]. For this client, the CRAT is funded with) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 10.50 Tf
0.145 0.169 0.204 rg
1 0 0 1 52.00 602.00 Tm
($16,000,000.00, and the annuity is set at $800,000.00 annually, representing a 5.00% payout rate.) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 10.50 Tf
0.145 0.169 0.204 rg
1 0 0 1 52.00 588.00 Tm
(The trust is irrevocable, meaning the assets are permanently removed from the donor's control.) Tj
ET
BT
/F2 11.50 Tf
0.169 0.349 0.639 rg
1 0 0 1 52.00 566.00 Tm
(Charitable Deduction and Remainder Interest) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 10.50 Tf
0.145 0.169 0.204 rg
1 0 0 1 52.00 543.00 Tm
(The charitable deduction for a CRAT is calculated as the present value of the remainder interest) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 10.50 Tf
0.145 0.169 0.204 rg
1 0 0 1 52.00 529.00 Tm
(that will eventually pass to the charity. For this client, the charitable deduction amounts to) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 10.50 Tf
0.145 0.169 0.204 rg
1 0 0 1 52.00 515.00 Tm
($7,620,722.64, ensuring compliance with the requirement that the charitable remainder interest must) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 10.50 Tf
0.145 0.169 0.204 rg
1 0 0 1 52.00 501.00 Tm
(be at least 10% of the initial trust corpus [1].) Tj
ET
